3.1 Data importing and sorting(GPP, Precipitation, LAI)

loading data

control_ch <- read.csv("finaldata/c_chambers.csv", header = TRUE, sep = ",", dec = ".", row.names = 1)

partialh_ch <- read.csv("finaldata/ph_chambers.csv", header = TRUE, sep = ",", dec = ".", row.names = 1)

precipitation <- read.csv("CSV/rain.csv", header = TRUE, sep = ",", dec = ".")

rain16.17 <- read.csv("CSV/rain16_17.csv", header = TRUE, sep = ",", dec = ".", row.names = 1)

lai <- read.csv("CSV/lai_data.csv", header = TRUE, sep = ";", dec = ",")

  • Research Questions

  • How strongly partial harvest impacts ground floor GPP?

  • How different plant community response to PAR?

  • Does GPP in different chambers varies significantly, and what are the reasons behind?

  • How forest floor GPP of partial harvest and control sites respond to changing climatic variables?

I combined all six chambers measurements from both control and partial harvest site in to this file.

control_ch$Chambers <- factor(control_ch$Chambers)

partialh_ch$Chambers <- factor(partialh_ch$Chambers)

I create separate date variables for daily, monthly and yearly average calculations

control_ch$daily <- day(control_ch$Date)
control_ch$monthly <- month(control_ch$Date)
control_ch$yearly <- year(control_ch$Date)
partialh_ch$daily <- day(partialh_ch$Date)
partialh_ch$monthly <- month(partialh_ch$Date)
partialh_ch$yearly <- year(partialh_ch$Date)

GPP calculated from measured NEE and modeled R

control_ch$caculatedGPP <- - control_ch$Measured.NEE..mg.co2.m.2.h.1. + control_ch$Modelled.respiration..mg.co2.m.2.h.1.
partialh_ch$caculatedGPP <- - partialh_ch$Measured.NEE..mg.co2.m.2.h.1. + partialh_ch$Modelled.respiration..mg.co2.m.2.h.1.

Lets compare monthly mean gpp of both sites for entire experiments

Lets look at average daily gpp for each months separately

control_ch$daily_monthly <- paste(control_ch$daily, control_ch$monthly)
partialh_ch$daily_monthly <- paste(partialh_ch$daily, partialh_ch$monthly)

  summarise(mean1 = mean(caculatedGPP, na.rm = TRUE)))

p3 <- ggplot(dailygpp, aes(daily_monthly, mean1)) + 
  geom_point() +
  labs(x= "Days&months", y = "Average GPP", title = "Daily average GPP (calculated) of control chambers")

Some figures and statistics on GPP of different chambers

controlch_avg <-tibble(control_ch %>% group_by(Chambers) %>% summarise(mean1 = mean(Modelled.GPP..mg.co2.m.2.h.1., na.rm = TRUE), mean2 = mean(caculatedGPP, na.rm = TRUE)))

p5 <- ggplot(controlch_avg, aes(mean1, mean2)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm") + 
  theme(axis.title.x = element_text( size = 8),
axis.title.y = element_text(size = 8), plot.title = element_text(size=12)) +
  labs(x= "Average modelled GPP", y = "Average calculated GPP", title = "Averaged modeled GPP against calculated GPP of control chambers")

partialchavg <- tibble(partialh_ch %>% group_by(Chambers) %>% summarise(meanmo = mean(Modelled.GPP..mg.co2.m.2.h.1., na.rm = TRUE), meancal = mean(caculatedGPP, na.rm = TRUE)))

p6 <- ggplot(partialchavg, aes(meanmo, meancal)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm") + 
  labs(x= "Average modelled GPP", y = "Average calculated GPP", title = "Averaged modeled GPP against calculated GPP of partial harvest chambers")

grid.arrange(p5, p6, ncol = 1, nrow =2)

3.2 Precipitation, PAR, LAI, Temperature and GPP

precipitation30min <- precipitation %>% select(Date, Lettosuo.Precipitation.Screend.mm.30min.1.)
colnames(precipitation30min) <- c("Date", "rain.mm.30.min.1")
precipitation30min <- precipitation30min %>% mutate(Date = dmy_hm(Date))
colnames(rain16.17) <- c("Date", "rain.mm.30.min.1")

rain10.17 <- rbind(precipitation30min, rain16.17)

rain13_18 <- rain10.17 %>% filter(Date > "2013-05-15 00:00:00")


precipitation30min$daily <- day(precipitation30min$Date)
precipitation30min$monthly <- month(precipitation30min$Date)
precipitation30min$yearly <- year(precipitation30min$Date)
precipitation30min$dailymy <- paste(precipitation30min$daily, precipitation30min$monthly, precipitation30min$yearly)

dailygpp <- tibble(control_ch %>% group_by(daily) %>%
  summarise(mean1 = mean(Modelled.GPP..mg.co2.m.2.h.1., na.rm = TRUE)))

pre <- precipitation30min %>% group_by(dailymy) %>% summarise(dailyrain = sum(rain.mm.30.min.1, na.rm = TRUE))

p7 <- ggplot(pre, aes(dailymy, dailyrain)) +
  geom_point(size = 1) + 
  labs(x = "date", y = "mm rain/30min")
